# Cursor Rules for IQ LDS Project

## Documentation

All documentation is located in the `documentation/` folder. Refer to documentation files for detailed guides on:
- Component usage
- Navigation patterns
- Design system
- Page creation
- And more

## Design System

### Design Tokens
- Use CSS variables for theming (defined in `src/index.css`)
- Follow the spacing scale: multiples of 4px
- Use semantic color names: `primary`, `secondary`, `muted`, `destructive`
- Maintain consistent border radius: `rounded-md` (6px)

### Typography & Spacing
- Font sizes: Use Tailwind scale (text-xs through text-4xl)
- Font weights: `font-normal`, `font-medium`, `font-semibold`, `font-bold`
- Page padding: `py-8` or `py-12`
- Section spacing: `space-y-6` or `space-y-8`

## Component Usage

### Component Library
- Use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui`
- Style: `radix-nova`
- Icon library: `hugeicons`
- Prefer composition over configuration
- Maintain accessibility (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)

## Navigation Patterns

### Back Button
- Use `BackButton` component or `PageHeaderWithBack` pattern
- Specify custom destination with `href` prop
- See `documentation/navigation.md` for details

### Breadcrumbs
- Automatically generated from route in `GlobalHeader`
- Provide custom breadcrumbs via `breadcrumbs` prop
- Hide on mobile

### Page Tabs
- Use `PageHeaderWithTabs` for tabbed navigation
- Sync with URL search params for shareable links
- Limit to 2 levels of nesting

## Code Style

### TypeScript & React
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Functional components with hooks
- Prefer named exports
- Use `cn()` utility for className merging
- Handle loading and error states

### File Naming
- Components: `kebab-case.tsx`
- Pages: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Utilities: `kebab-case.ts`

### Import Organization
```tsx
// 1. React, 2. Third-party, 3. UI components, 4. Utilities, 5. Types
import * as React from "react"
import { Component } from "library"
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
import type { ComponentProps } from "@/types"
```

## Path Aliases
- `@/components` - Components directory
- `@/lib` - Utility functions
- `@/hooks` - Custom React hooks

## Accessibility
- Keyboard accessible interactive elements
- Semantic HTML
- ARIA labels where needed
- WCAG AA color contrast
- Test with screen readers

## Performance
- Lazy load heavy components
- Optimize images
- Minimize bundle size
- Use React.memo for expensive components

## Project Configuration
- Style: `radix-nova` (shadcn/ui)
- Icon Library: `hugeicons`
- Base Color: `neutral`
- CSS Variables: Enabled
- TypeScript: Enabled
- RSC: Disabled
